FBIS4-32257 "dreeu120__a94003" FBIS-EEU-94-120-A Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 ANNEX Albania Omonia Leader Demands `Autonomy' for Minority Omonia Leader Demands `Autonomy' for Minority AU2106161094 Tirana ATA in English 1006 GMT 21 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2106161094 Tirana ATA English BFN [Text] Tirana, June 20 (ATA) -- Continuing to publish various documents proving the anti-Albanian activity of the Greek chauvinistic circles, the newspaper REPUBLIKA, in its latest issue, carried a letter by Sotir Qirjazati, chairman of Omonia, sent to the Greek Premier Mitsotakis on May 30, 1992. Through this letter, the chairman of Omonia, demands self-determination and autonomy of the Greek minority in Albania. Also, he considers the U.S.A. and some European countries as enemies, only because they are allies of Albania.
